      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Sift the flour, mixed spice, baking powder, and salt into a large bowl. Add the cold butter and rub in with fingertips until the mixture resembles coarse breadcrumbs. Stir in the sugar and currants. Beat the egg with the milk and add to the mixture, stirring with a fork until a dough just comes together; add a little more milk if needed. Wrap and refrigerate for 30 minutes.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 190°C conventional (170°C fan). Line two baking trays with baking paper. Roll the dough on a lightly floured surface to about 5 mm thick. Cut into rounds with a 6 to 7 cm cutter and place on the lined trays with a little space between each. Re-roll the offcuts. Bake for 16 to 20 minutes until deep golden. Transfer to a rack immediately and cool completely.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
